    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A sulfate of copper, blue crystals in hydrous form, white when dehydrated. Copper sulfate is used as a preservative for wood, leather and paper; as a mordant and dye for textiles; as a biocide, and for a wide range of other purposes.  </Note_Text>
